	abstract = {The RANdom SAmple Consensus (RANSAC) algorithm proposed by Fischler and Bolles 1 is a general parameter estimation approach designed to cope with a large proportion of outliers in the input data. Unlike many of the common robust estimation techniques such as M-estimators and least-median squares that have been adopted by the computer vision community from the statistics literature, RANSAC was developed from within the computer vision community.},
